From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Akanksha Hotta <akanksha.hotta@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 16:33:21 +0530
Subject: drm/pagemap: guard drm_pagemap_put() definition against
 header inline

When BPM_DRM_PAGEMAP_PUT_NOT_PRESENT is defined (kernel lacks
drm_pagemap_put), drm_pagemap.h provides a static inline fallback.
The unconditional definition of drm_pagemap_put() in drm_pagemap.c
then conflicts with that inline, causing a redefinition error.

Guard the .c definition with BPM_DRM_PAGEMAP_PUT_NOT_PRESENT
so that:
- On kernels without drm_pagemap_put: the header inline is used.
- On kernels with drm_pagemap_put: the full implementation (including
  drm_pagemap_shrinker_might_lock) is compiled and exported.

Signed-off-by: Akanksha Hotta <akanksha.hotta@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c
index 1b1e7bd..a35a1b0 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c
@@ -923,6 +923,7 @@ int drm_pagemap_init(struct drm_pagemap *dpagemap,
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_pagemap_init);
 
+#ifndef BPM_DRM_PAGEMAP_PUT_NOT_PRESENT
 /**
  * drm_pagemap_put() - Put a struct drm_pagemap reference
  * @dpagemap: Pointer to a struct drm_pagemap object.
@@ -938,6 +939,7 @@ void drm_pagemap_put(struct drm_pagemap *dpagemap)
 	}
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_pagemap_put);
+#endif /* BPM_DRM_PAGEMAP_PUT_NOT_PRESENT */
 
 /**
  * drm_pagemap_evict_to_ram() - Evict GPU SVM range to RAM
-- 
